FBIS4-5322 "dreas069_h_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-069 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Minister Announces New Central Bank Governor Minister Announces New Central Bank Governor BK0804133994 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in English 1300 GMT 8 Apr 94 BK0804133994 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network English BFN [Excerpt] Malayan Banking Berhad's [Maybank] managing director Encik [Mr.] Ahmad Mohamed Don has been appointed as the new governor of Bank Negara [Central Bank] effective 1 May. He will replace Tan Sri Jaffar Hussein, who has opted for early retirement after taking responsibility for Bank Negara's massive losses in (?forward) transactions in the foreign exchange market in 1992 and 1993. Encik Ahmad, 47, has been appointed for a three-year period. Finance Minister Datuk Sri Anwar Ibrahim announced this in a statement today. Apppointed as managing director of Maybank since 1 January 1991, the company under his stewardship has emerged as the country's leading bank. The banking group was the number one bank among commercial banks in the country in terms of assets, deposits, shareholders' fund, and precash profit in 1993 and 1994. [passage omitted on new central bank governor's education and career]
